From 8b7528a733f2cd570a9e6960d036c81d034379ba Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 11:12:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(access): mint invite-key Orbit tokens against real
 apiTokenCreate schema
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Orbit ApiTokenCreateInput has name/scopes/lifespan/limitResources only ‚Äî no
userId. We were sending userId plus type:"Project" (enum is lowercase
"project"), so apiTokenCreate always failed. Portal login masked this via
admin PAT fallback; invite keys use forbidAdminFallback and returned 200 with
orbitToken:"" which Lite correctly rejects.

- Drop userId from the mint mutation; use type:"project" for limitResources
- Invite-key sessions fail with HTTP 503 on mint failure (never empty token)
- Portal / full-connector path unchanged (admin fallback still allowed)
---
 docs/INVITE_KEYS.md    | 10 ++++++---
 src/access/session.ts  | 50 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----------
 src/orbit/mint.ts      | 45 ++++++++++++++++++++++---------------
 src/tests/mint.test.ts | 19 ++++++++++++++++
 4 files changed, 91 insertions(+), 33 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 src/tests/mint.test.ts

diff --git a/docs/INVITE_KEYS.md b/docs/INVITE_KEYS.md
index 68d28c7..0b12c62 100644
--- a/docs/INVITE_KEYS.md
+++ b/docs/INVITE_KEYS.md
@@ -131,9 +131,13 @@ When `portal_adapter=mock` (prism-dev):
 
 1. **Manifest** ‚Äî client DenyIfNotAllowed is UX only; invite keys never set
    `orbitBlanketAccess=true` and never include `receive` / `create_project`.
-2. **Orbit token** ‚Äî minted with `limitResources` = key project ids and scopes
-   derived from allowed functions (`streams:write` / `objects:write` for send
-   paths). Production must use real `apiTokenCreate` (`ORBIT_MINT_FALLBACK=0`).
+2. **Orbit token** ‚Äî minted via `apiTokenCreate` with `limitResources` = key
+   project ids (`type: project`) and scopes derived from allowed functions.
+   The Orbit schema has **no** `userId` on `ApiTokenCreateInput` ‚Äî the token is
+   owned by the PRISM Orbit admin PAT and scoped by `limitResources`. Invite-key
+   sessions **never** fall back to the raw admin PAT; mint failure returns HTTP
+   503 (not 200 with an empty `orbitToken`). Portal / full-connector login is
+   unchanged and may still use the admin fallback when minting fails.
 3. **Revocation** ‚Äî key revoke marks sessions + minted tokens `revokedAt`.
 4. **Audit** ‚Äî `invite_key.created_by`, `invite_key_redemption` rows, session
    `invite_key_id`, manifest `userId` / `inviteKeyId`.
